":"Ganesh Vaideeswaran", "email":"Ganesh.Vaideeswaran@marklogic.com"}, "change":{"tofixin":{"from":"6.0-3", "to":"6.0-4"}}, "files":[], "show":true}, {"time":"2013-06-24T14:58:14.173993-07:00", "updatedBy":{"username":"sbrooks", "name":"Scott Brooks", "email":"Scott.Brooks@marklogic.com"}, "change":{}, "files":[], "show":true, "comment":"All IE related issues with AppBuilder:\r\nhttp://bugtrack.marklogic.com/17273\r\nhttp://bugtrack.marklogic.com/16824\r\nhttp://bugtrack.marklogic.com/20096\r\nare due to the XForms library being used as the core underpinnings of these apps.  Unfortunately they were built before I got here by some outside contractors + some internal employees who are no longer with ML.  \r\n\r\nI briefly looked into updating the XForms library sometime in 2012 (I even spoke with the creator of the library) but were unable to get the latest version to work with our existing code.   Management is aware that this legacy code is badly in need of modernization.  We just need to be given the time or resources to take on a rewrite of it.\r\n\r\nSo on Nov. 14th, 2012, Ganesh wrote \"We do not support AppBuilder in IE8 (compat view or otherwise)\".  For some reason the bug was re-opened anyway.  \r\n\r\nAs far as I know, this policy is still true, so I'm sending this back to Megha to clarify that point and close if in fact we no longer need to support IE8.  Otherwise, we need to track as an external deficiency due to XForms still being used on these legacy apps."}, {"time":"2013-06-24T14:58:14.173993-07:00", "updatedBy":{"username":"sbrooks", "name":"Scott Brooks", "email":"Scott.Brooks@marklogic.com"}, "change":{"assignTo":{"from":{"username":"sbrooks", "name":"Scott Brooks", "email":"Scott.Brooks@marklogic.com"}, "to":{"username":"msarma", "name":"Meghalim Sarma", "email":"msarma@marklogic.com"}}}, "files":[], "show":true}, {"time":"2013-07-12T11:06:48.478855-07:00", "updatedBy":{"username":"rpelton", "name":"Rick Pelton", "email":"rick.pelton@marklogic.com